# Breadcrumb

Navigation trail that shows hierarchy.

## Basic Usage
### Breadcrumb Trail
Provide a quick sense of place.
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="BreadcrumbBreadcrumbTrailDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <template>
    <TxBreadcrumb
      :items="[
        { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
        { label: 'Library', href: '/library' },
        { label: 'Data' },
      ]"
    />
  </template>
---
:::
## API (Lite)
::TuffPropsTable
---
rows:
  - name: items
    type: "BreadcrumbItem[]"
    default: '[]'
    description: Breadcrumb items
  - name: separatorIcon
    type: string
    default: "'chevron-right'"
    description: Separator icon
---
:::

## Item Contract

::TuffPropsTable
---
rows:
  - name: label
    type: string
    default: '-'
    description: Breadcrumb text
  - name: href
    type: string
    default: '-'
    description: Link target; current and disabled items do not render as links
  - name: icon
    type: string
    default: '-'
    description: Leading icon
  - name: disabled
    type: boolean
    default: 'false'
    description: Disable navigation and click events for the item
---
:::

## Events

::TuffPropsTable
---
rows:
  - name: click
    type: '(item: BreadcrumbItem, index: number) => void'
    default: '-'
    description: Triggered when users click a non-current, non-disabled item without href
---
:::

## Interaction Contract

- The last item always represents the current page, renders as a non-link element, and exposes `aria-current="page"`.
- Non-current, non-disabled items with `href` render as native links.
- `disabled` items render as non-link elements, expose `aria-disabled="true"`, and do not emit `click`.

